git init:   Initialize a new, empty Git Repo or to reinitialize an Exisiting one

git remote add origin -> The command git remote add origin <URL> is used to connect a local Git repo
                         to a remote server for the first time. It creates a "bookmark" or 
                         shorthand alias named origin that points to the remote repository's 
                         full web address.
                         It can be verified by typing git -v command

git push -u origin dev -> what does -u?
                            Does 2 thing:
                                Publish the branch(Git repo)
                                Making the dev branch as upstream branch(In future if i give
                                git pull or git push my changes will be pushed or pulled from dev branch
                                its like a shortcut instead of entirely typing git pull origin dev
                                I can do this. If i need to make other branch as upstream branch 
                                I need to reconfigure that git pull -u origin feature1)

